    "DRI [29] with 84.4% F1 (+11.9% absolute improvement) and ART [53] with 58.8% accuracy (+7.2% absolute improvement) (#RQ4).",
    "In particular, models for tasks with small datasets and classes with few labelled examples benefit significantly from models of other tasks.",
    "We investigated the differences and problems of MULT ALL and MULT GRP through multiple examples.",
    "Our analysis suggests that the classes of the different dataset annotation schemes are semantically related, even though the datasets come from different domains and have different text types (#RQ1).",
    "This semantic relatedness is an important prerequisite for transfer learning in NLP tasks [58,62,69].Finally, we have presented an approach to semi-automatically identify semantically related classes from different datasets to support manual comparison and inspection of different annotation schemes across domains."
